### 2. Module Configurations (`modules/vpc-own/`)

#### `modules/vpc-own/variable.tf`

Defines the structure for our current configuration maps.

```hcl
variable "multi_sub_details" {
  type = map(object({
    cidr_block_own = string
  }))
  
}

variable "own_vpc_details" {
  type = object({
    config1_vpc_cidr = string
    Name=string
  })
  
}

```

#### `modules/vpc-own/vpc.tf`

Handles the base VPC network layer.

```hcl
resource "aws_vpc" "own_vpc" {
  cidr_block = var.own_vpc_details.config1_vpc_cidr
  
}

```

#### `modules/vpc-own/subnets.tf`

Currently uses two explicit, separate resource blocks to build the subnets out of the old variable map.

```hcl
resource "aws_subnet" "own_subet1" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.own_vpc.id
  cidr_block = var.multi_sub_details["subnet_1"].cidr_block_own
  
}
resource "aws_subnet" "own_subet2" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.own_vpc.id
  cidr_block = var.multi_sub_details["subnet_2"].cidr_block_own
  
}
